gw.api.builder

Class AccountBuilder

  • java.lang.Object
    • gw.api.databuilder.DataBuilder<Account,AccountBuilder>
      • gw.api.builder.AccountBuilder
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ValueGenerator<Account>

    public class AccountBuilder
extends DataBuilder<Account,AccountBuilder>
    Builder class for creating a new Account in PolicyCenter. The simplest usage is 
       new AccountBuilder().createAndCommit()
    which creates an account that is sufficiently populated for many purposes.

    • Constructor Detail

      • AccountBuilder

        public AccountBuilder()
        Constructs an AccountBuilder with a default account holder. Calls AccountBuilder(boolean), which fills in numerous defaults.

      • AccountBuilder

        public AccountBuilder(boolean createDefaultAccountHolder)
        Create an AccountBuilder. A default account holder will be created from a new PersonBuilder if createDefaultAccountHolder is true. If createDefaultAccountHolder is false, the caller should supply an account holder by calling withAccountHolderContact(Contact) or withAccountHolderContact(ContactBuilder).

        The following defaults are provided:

        (from domain SIC)
        FieldValue
        StatusPending
        AccountNumber(generated, will start with Test-)
        AccountOrgTypeCommon Ownership
        BusinessDescription"business description"
        IndustryCode
        PreferredSettlementCurrencydefault application currency
        PreferredCoverageCurrencydefault application currency
        Producer,ProducerCodeArmstrong, one of their codes
        PrimaryLocationCreated from the account holder contact
        The populator for this builder runs at maximum priority (i.e. last), so a subclass which wants to override behavior will not be able to do it by countermanding the actions of the populator.
        Parameters:
        createDefaultAccountHolder - if this is true, a default account holder will be created.

      • withAccountHolderContact

        public AccountBuilder withAccountHolderContact(ContactBuilder contactBuilder)
        Uses a contact builder to create a main account. AccountBuilder's default behavior is to automatically create a valid account holder, even if this method is not called. To specify your own contact, you must construct the builder using new AccountBuilder(false).
        Parameters:
        contactBuilder - The contact builder to create an account with.

      • withAccountHolderContact

        public AccountBuilder withAccountHolderContact(Contact contact)
        Uses the passed in contact to create a main account contact. AccountBuilder's default behavior is to automatically create a valid account holder, even if this method is not called. To specify your own contact, you must construct the builder using new AccountBuilder(false).
        Parameters:
        contact - The contact to create an account with.
